Invention:  Automobile
Year:       1885
Inventor:   Karl Benz
Country:    Germany
Category:   Transportation
Description:Gasoline-powered self-propelled vehicle
Impact:     Transformed cities, suburbs, economy; petroleum age

Invention:  Telegraph
Year:       1837
Inventor:   Samuel Morse
Country:    USA
Category:   Communication
Description:Electrical coded message transmission
Impact:     First rapid long-distance communication

Invention:  Printing Press
Year:       1440
Inventor:   Gutenberg
Country:    Germany
Category:   Communication
Description:Movable metal type for mass printing
Impact:     Democratized knowledge; enabled Reformation and science

============================================================
  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     GAN
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Generator vs discriminator adversarial training
Year:        2014
Researchers: Ian Goodfellow et al.
Applications:Image synthesis, deepfakes, augmentation
Related:     Mode collapse, discriminator, generator

Concept:     Reinforcement Learning
Category:    Paradigm
Definition:  Agent learns from environment interaction to maximize reward
Year:        1950
Researchers: Bellman; Sutton/Barto
Applications:Games, robotics, recommendations, LLM alignment
Related:     Reward, policy, value function, Q-learning

Concept:     Vector Database
Category:    Infrastructure
Definition:  Stores high-dimensional embeddings for similarity search
Year:        2019
Researchers: Pinecone/Weaviate/Faiss
Applications:RAG, semantic search, recommendation
Related:     ANN search, HNSW, cosine similarity

